Description: Ph.D. scholar in English
Headquarters Regions: Greater Boston Area, East Coast, New England
Full Description: Epernicus is a professional networking platform for scientists. Thousands of researchers around the world are using Epernicus to connect with colleagues in their real world scientific networks and to find the expertise and people they need to advance their work. What makes Epernicus different? - Our rich profiles capture the key attributes of a scientist such as their training, publications, and scientific genealogy (mentorship history). - We automatically assemble a scientist's real world network including their research groups, departments, institutions, and alumni networks. - We enable researchers to define their "assets" - the topics, materials, and methods in which they have expertise - thereby making it easier to find scientists with specific skills. - We help to connect scientists not only from academia but also from private industry and government research institutions. For more details, see: http://epernicus.wordpress.com/2008/06/23/why-should-you-join-epernicus-if-youre-on-linkedin/ Who started Epernicus? - Vivek Murthy, MD, MBA (co-founder and chairman) - In addition to serving as chairman of Epernicus, Vivek works part-time as an attending physician at Brigham and Women's Hospital and as an instructor at Harvard Medical School.  During his medical training, he conducted research in microbiology with Gerald Pier (Harvard), and later engaged in health services and public health research initiatives with Cary Gross and David Katz (Yale). - Mikhail Shapiro, Ph.D. (co-founder and director) - During his undergraduate years at Brown University, Mikhail co-founded Cyberkinetics Neurotechnology Systems, Inc, a publicly traded neuroscience-focused medical technology company.  He later completed his PhD at MIT under the supervision of Robert Langer, PhD where he developed molecular sensors for non-invasive imaging of the brain. - Eric Silberstein (co-founder and CEO) - Prior to Epernicus, Eric was founder and Chairman of Idiom Technologies (acquired by SDL). - Ezra Freedman (co-founder and CTO) - Prior to Epernicus, Ezra was VP, Technology for Schematic, a leading Los Angeles-based interactive agency that develops interface and technology solutions for the Web, television and mobile devices.
Industry Groups: Biotechnology, Health Care, Science and Engineering
Founders: Eric Silberstein, Ezra Freedman, Mikhail Shapiro, Vivek Murthy

Description: Qupé focuses on cool climate expressions of Rhône varietals due to a distinctive geographical feature that sets.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Qupé focuses on cool climate expressions of Rhône varietals due to a distinctive geographical feature that sets them apart from most other regions of California, as all vineyards are all located in East-West valleys (vs North-South) which function as open windows to the cool Pacific Ocean. The benefit to the vineyards of being along the coast and running East-West is that the cold, moist air gets pulled in and creates a layer of morning cloud cover over the vines which reduces temperatures and sun exposure on the grapes. This is why cool climate varieties excel in the coastal regions of the Central Coast and allows Qupé to focus on cool climate expressions of Rhone varietals. East-West valleys on the Central Coast that Qupé sources from include Edna Valley, Arroyo Grande Valley, Santa Maria Valley, Los Alamos Valley and Santa Rita Hills/Santa Ynez Valley.

Description: Gamestaq is an online marketplace for gamers to buy and sell games through the site.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Gamestaq is a streamlined P2P marketplace for users to buy and sell their games directly with other gamers at fair prices. The site aggregates used game prices from around the net and generates a single fair-market-value for every game. Sellers simply post their games at the set market value and their games sell on a FIFO basis. Buyers shop for games just as they would a standard e-commerce site and transact with the seller at the same established market price.  Gamestaq facilitates each transaction so the buyer and seller never need to interact with each other. From capturing the buyer's credit card, to providing the pre-paid shipping label, Gamestaq provides its users all of the benefits a P2P marketplace offers, minus the hassles. With this model, gamers are able to buy/sell at the actual market value of their games.
